=== 申請城市階段 ===
東京在2011年7月16日時，被[[日本奧林匹克委員會|日本奧林匹克委員會]]選為角逐2020年夏季奧運會主辦權的城市。獲選的主要原因是[[2011年日本東北地方太平洋近海地震|2011年日本東北地方太平洋近海地震]]對東日本重創後，以再次邁進的理念，展現復興的力量。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/07/15/olympics-tokyo-bid-idUSL3E7IF1XH20110715 |title=Olympics-Tokyo tiptoes into 2020 bid race |access-date=2013-05-01 |archive-date=2015-09-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924154210/http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/07/15/olympics-tokyo-bid-idUSL3E7IF1XH20110715 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>在此之前，[[廣島|廣島]]也有意爭取主辦權，但最終選擇放棄。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.gamesbids.com/eng/olympic_bids/future_bids_2016/1216135715.html |title=Hiroshima Opts Out Of 2020 Olympic Bid |access-date=2013-05-01 |archive-date=2012-09-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120918033328/http://www.gamesbids.com/eng/olympic_bids/future_bids_2016/1216135715.html |dead-url=yes }}</ref>

2011年11月底，申辦委員會正式成立，以當時的日本[[內閣總理大臣|內閣總理大臣]][[野田佳彥|野田佳彥]]為首，由64名成員所組成。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.gamesbids.com/eng/olympic_bids/2020_bid_news/1216135975.html |title=New Council Boosts Tokyo 2020 |access-date=2013-05-01 |archive-date=2012-01-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120105201726/http://www.gamesbids.com/eng/olympic_bids/2020_bid_news/1216135975.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>2011年11月30日，發表東京2020年夏季奧運會申辦標誌。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.gamesbids.com/eng/olympic_bids/2020_bid_news/1216135981.html |title=Tokyo 2020 Showcases New Olympic Bid Logo |access-date=2013-05-01 |archive-date=2012-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120103195411/http://www.gamesbids.com/eng/olympic_bids/2020_bid_news/1216135981.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>申辦預算方面，預估為7,500萬元，比上一次巴西申辦[[2016年夏季奧運|2016年夏季奧運]]會少了約一半。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.gamesbids.com/eng/olympic_bids/2020_bid_news/1216135986.html |title=Tokyo To Reduce 2020 Olympics Bid Budget |access-date=2013-05-01 |archive-date=2012-01-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120118215808/http://www.gamesbids.com/eng/olympic_bids/2020_bid_news/1216135986.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>日本奧林匹克委員會會長竹田恆和則表示，舉辦奧運會將會對東京產生200億的經濟效益。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.gamesbids.com/eng/olympic_bids/2020_bid_news/1216136157.html |title=Tokyo 2020 Games Could Generate $2 Billion |access-date=2013-05-01 |archive-date=2012-05-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120505024418/http://www.gamesbids.com/eng/olympic_bids/2020_bid_news/1216136157.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

2011年12月初，日本[[日本眾議院|眾議院]]與[[日本參議院|參議院]]通過決議，將全力支持並和東京申奧合作。決議中也提到主辦奧運的幫助，以及代表日本從[[東日本大震災|東日本大震災]]重新站起的象徵。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.gamesbids.com/eng/olympic_bids/2020_bid_news/1216135988.html |title=Tokyo 2020 Gets Another Boost |access-date=2013-05-01 |archive-date=2012-01-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120119002859/http://www.gamesbids.com/eng/olympic_bids/2020_bid_news/1216135988.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.gamesbids.com/eng/olympic_bids/2020_bid_news/1216135989.html |title=Japan's Upper House Adopts Tokyo 2020 Resolution |access-date=2013-05-01 |archive-date=2012-01-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120118222135/http://www.gamesbids.com/eng/olympic_bids/2020_bid_news/1216135989.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>在內閣方面，也給予強力的支持。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.gamesbids.com/eng/olympic_bids/2020_bid_news/1216135994.html |title=National Government Backs Tokyo 2020 |access-date=2013-05-01 |archive-date=2012-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120103150326/http://www.gamesbids.com/eng/olympic_bids/2020_bid_news/1216135994.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

在2012年1月的調查顯示，接近66%的民眾贊同申辦。<ref name="#1">{{Cite web |url=http://www.gamesbids.com/eng/olympic_bids/future_bids_2016/1216136051.html |title=Tokyo 2020 Gets Major Support |access-date=2013-05-01 |archive-date=2012-07-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120725202337/http://www.gamesbids.com/eng/olympic_bids/future_bids_2016/1216136051.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

2012年2月，申辦單位任命荒木田裕子（[[1976年夏季奧林匹克運動會|1976年奧運會]]女子排球金牌成員）為理事，<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.gamesbids.com/eng/olympic_bids/2020_bid_news/1216136068.html |title=Tokyo 2020 Appoints Gold Medalist As Sports Director |access-date=2013-05-01 |archive-date=2012-02-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120203072435/http://www.gamesbids.com/eng/olympic_bids/2020_bid_news/1216136068.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>江上綾乃（[[2000年夏季奧林匹克運動會|2000年奧運會]]銀牌得主） 為網路和社群媒體宣傳的負責人。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.aroundtherings.com/articles/view.aspx?id=39580 |title=Team GB Uniform Reaction; Tokyo 2020 Addition; Generations for Peace First |access-date=2013-05-01 |archive-date=2012-03-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120325142527/http://aroundtherings.com/articles/view.aspx?id=39580 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

=== 候選城市階段 ===
[[File:Announce_of_Bidding_2020_Summer_Olympics_at_Tokyo_Big_Sight.jpg|thumb]]的宣傳布條]]

5月23日，[[國際奧林匹克委員會|IOC]]正式遴選東京為三個[[2020年夏季奧林匹克運動會|2020年夏季奧林匹克運動會]]候選城市的其中之一。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.olympic.org/news?articleid=160523&articlenewsgroup=-1 |title=IOC selects three cities as Candidates for the 2020 Olympic Games |access-date=2013-06-02 |archive-date=2015-04-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150430030307/http://www.olympic.org/news?articleid=160523&articlenewsgroup=-1 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

6月，一項調查顯示東京若能主辦奧運，將可創造超過150,000個的工作機會。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.insidethegames.biz/olympics/summer-olympics/2020/17217-a-tokyo-win-qwould-create-more-than-150000-jobsq-says-new-research |title=A Tokyo win "would create more than 150,000 jobs", says new research |access-date=2013-06-02 |archive-date=2013-12-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131225143818/http://www.insidethegames.biz/olympics/summer-olympics/2020/17217-a-tokyo-win-qwould-create-more-than-150000-jobsq-says-new-research |dead-url=no }}</ref>7月，決定對外的宣傳標語是「Discover Tomorrow」。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.insidethegames.biz/olympics/summer-olympics/2020/17779-tokyo-2020-bid-team-unveils-qdiscover-tomorrowq-slogan |title=Tokyo 2020 bid team unveils "Discover Tomorrow" slogan |access-date=2013-06-02 |archive-date=2014-01-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140126014336/http://www.insidethegames.biz/olympics/summer-olympics/2020/17779-tokyo-2020-bid-team-unveils-qdiscover-tomorrowq-slogan |dead-url=no }}</ref>

11月，[[2012年夏季奧林匹克運動會|倫敦奧運會]]過後，再度針對市民的支持意願進行調查，結果67%的東京居民贊成主辦奧運。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.insidethegames.biz/olympics/summer-olympics/304-2020-bidding-sports/1011570-public-support-grows-for-tokyo-2020-after-london-2012 |title=存档副本 |access-date=2013-06-02 |archive-date=2013-12-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131225131125/http://www.insidethegames.biz/olympics/summer-olympics/304-2020-bidding-sports/1011570-public-support-grows-for-tokyo-2020-after-london-2012 |dead-url=no }}</ref>此外，公開主場地[[國立霞丘陸上競技場|國立霞丘陸上競技場]]的改造設計圖，此體育場也將舉辦[[2019年世界盃橄欖球賽|2019年世界盃橄欖球賽]]。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.espnscrum.com/scrum/rugby/story/173144.html |title=Dazzling re-design for 2019 World Cup final venue |access-date=2013-06-02 |archive-date=2015-03-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150323001613/http://www.espnscrum.com/scrum/rugby/story/173144.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

2013年1月7日，東京向IOC提交候選的相關文件。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.olympic.org/news/2020-candidate-cities-deliver-candidature-files/187656 |title=2020 Candidate Cities deliver Candidature Files Public support grows for Tokyo 2020 after London 2012 |access-date=2013-06-02 |archive-date=2016-03-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305002743/http://www.olympic.org/news/2020-candidate-cities-deliver-candidature-files/187656 |dead-url=no }}</ref> 

1月的新調查顯示，73%的居民支持申辦奧運，並有其他調查的支持率達到78%，<ref>[http://www.aroundtherings.com/articles/view.aspx?id=42216 Latest Poll Confirms Strong Support for Tokyo 2020]</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.insidethegames.biz/olympics/summer-olympics/2020/1012683-support-for-tokyo-2020-campaign-at-new-high-survey-shows |title=Support for Tokyo 2020 campaign at new high survey shows |access-date=2013-06-02 |archive-date=2013-12-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131224125746/http://www.insidethegames.biz/olympics/summer-olympics/2020/1012683-support-for-tokyo-2020-campaign-at-new-high-survey-shows |dead-url=no }}</ref>意味著支持的民眾正在上升，<ref name="#1"/>[[讀賣新聞|讀賣新聞]]的民調更有83%的國民贊成。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.insidethegames.biz/olympics/summer-olympics/2020/1013147-support-growing-for-tokyo-2020-bid-new-survey-claims |title=Support growing for Tokyo 2020 bid new survey claims |access-date=2013-06-02 |archive-date=2015-03-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150329005324/http://www.insidethegames.biz/olympics/summer-olympics/2020/1013147-support-growing-for-tokyo-2020-bid-new-survey-claims |dead-url=no }}</ref>在上屆的申辦，東京於一項調查中僅有56%的居民支持主辦。<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/feedarticle/8486157|title=Tokyo bid suffers in IOC support poll of residents|publisher=Guardian.co.uk|date=2009-05-02|accessdate=2013-02-01|archive-date=2009-05-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090517070303/http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/feedarticle/8486157|dead-url=no}}</ref>

3月4日至3月7日，IOC的考核委員會成員造訪東京。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.tokyo2020.jp/en/news/index.php?mode=page&id=624 |title=Tokyo 2020 Leaders Kick-off Evaluation Commission Visit |access-date=2013-06-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150623140908/http://tokyo2020.jp/en/news/index.php?mode=page&id=624 |archive-date=2015-06-23 |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://tokyo2020.jp/en/news/index.php?mode=page&id=651 |title=IOC Evaluation Commission Visit - Day3 |access-date=2013-06-02 |archive-date=2015-09-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150910022435/http://tokyo2020.jp/en/news/index.php?mode=page&id=651 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

9月7日，正式獲選為2020年夏季奧林匹克運動會主辦城市，是東京相隔56年以來第二次承辦賽事。

